
Usage:
scorep-config <command> [<options>]
  Commands:
   --cflags  prints additional compiler flags. They already contain the
             include flags.
   --inc     prints the include flags. They are already contained in the
             output of the --cflags command
   --libs    prints the required linker flags
   --cc      prints the C compiler name
   --cxx     prints the C++ compiler name
   --fc      prints the Fortran compiler name
   --help    prints this usage information
   --version prints the version number of the scorep package

  Options:
   --seq|--omp|--mpi|--hyb
            specifys the mode: seqential, OpenMP, MPI, or hybrid (MPI + OpenMP)
            Takes effect only for the --libs command. The default mode is MPI.

   --config=<config_file>
            Allows to specify a configuration file which overrides the data
            specified at build time of the tool.

   --user|--nouser
            Specifies whether manual user instrumentation is used. On default
            user instrumentation is disabled.

   --compiler|--nocompiler
            Specifies whether compiler instrumentation is used. On default
            compiler instrumentation is enabled.

   --fortran   Specifies that the required flags are for the Fortran compiler.


